{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4d38917a-da78-46bb-9555-d5aed853ddaa","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as \"skipped\" in results (not failed), and the reason string appears in test output/reports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"862e3b01-0350-4fd9-84c9-2147b628ea1f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to invoke tools or skills.","outputTokens":227,"requestId":"E3C0:2CBD0C:17A9244:1A64947:6A0523D6"},"id":"151e742d-430d-41ad-8a43-b6ed4dc0394e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:22:36.635Z","parentId":"3e9050bd-02fc-46a5-bdb8-79725eafc626"}
